1
00:00:19,167 --> 00:00:20,933
This is just my opinion.

2
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,667
I really feel that
there's something with Mikoy.

3
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:24,900
What do you mean something?

4
00:00:24,967 --> 00:00:28,000
What else? He still likes you.

5
00:00:28,067 --> 00:00:28,700
Who's there?

6
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,700
Why didn't you lock the door?

7
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,200
I'm leaving...

8
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:35,600
This is sickening.

9
00:00:35,667 --> 00:00:36,900
You can't trust that guy.

10
00:00:36,967 --> 00:00:38,667
Babe, please don't act
like a child.

11
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:40,067
We've already talked about this.

12
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:43,733
I know but sleeping beside him
is not part of the deal.

13
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,333
He might do something to you.

14
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:46,367
He's going crazy.

15
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:47,767
You know we're quits already.

16
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:49,567
I fooled you before.

17
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:52,367
You saw me naked today, right?

18
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:54,867
- It's fair.
- Celeste!

19
00:00:54,933 --> 00:00:56,233
Mikoy!

20
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,233
May-May, you should slow down
with your drinking.

21
00:00:58,300 --> 00:01:00,533
I have no plans of taking home
two drunk women.

22
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:04,600
I saw everything.

23
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:06,467
As in everything?

24
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:09,367
Yes, in his naked glory.

25
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:13,400
Alcohol really does something
different.

26
00:01:15,067 --> 00:01:17,600
Earlier,
you could not look at me.

27
00:01:17,667 --> 00:01:20,167
Now you're talking
as if I don't exist.

28
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:21,567
I need to pee.

29
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:23,767
I'll just go to the bathroom.
Is that okay?

30
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:29,767
They say that if you're drunk,
you can say what you want

31
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:31,267
that you can't say
if you're normal.

32
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,833
Okay, game. Let's test.

33
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:39,667
Pretend that we didn't
part ways.

34
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:41,900
Okay, it didn't happen.

35
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,233
Tonito boy didn't come
into my life.

36
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:47,933
We're still a couple
and I'm like this.

37
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,767
Like this, like me
and all that jazz.

38
00:01:52,233 --> 00:01:53,667
Will you still love me?

39
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:58,600
Why are you speechless?

40
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:08,567
Last night was terrible.

41
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:10,400
I was so wasted.

42
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:11,933
I drank a lot.

43
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,133
You don't remember what you did
and you've said?

44
00:02:15,233 --> 00:02:17,000
Did I say something distasteful?

45
00:02:17,067 --> 00:02:19,767
It's more like naughty.

46
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:23,100
- Naughty?
- No, more of kinky.

47
00:02:23,167 --> 00:02:24,567
Kinky?

48
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:25,933
- No.
- You shouldn't drink

49
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,733
what you can't handle so you
won't do anything outrageous.

50
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,400
I don't feel well.

51
00:02:30,467 --> 00:02:32,367
It's like I have a fever.

52
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:33,633
I'm hot.

53
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:35,233
You're not hot today.

54
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:36,567
You were hot last night.

55
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:40,267
Mikoy, what's with you?

56
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:41,233
Don't be like that.

57
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:56,533
My goodness, this is beautiful!

58
00:02:56,600 --> 00:03:00,133
I'm in awe.

59
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:01,500
Wow!

60
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,300
You have a headache earlier.

61
00:03:04,367 --> 00:03:06,267
What? Let's go home?
Take a rest.

62
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:09,333
No, I feel better now.

63
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,700
It's beautiful here.

64
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,133
Do you like it?

65
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,300
I love it.

66
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:18,600
Wait, why did you bring me here?

67
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:20,300
This is where we'll do
community service?

68
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,667
Yes.

69
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:23,867
We're going to pick sunflowers

70
00:03:23,933 --> 00:03:26,100
because there will be an event
later in the city hall.

71
00:03:26,167 --> 00:03:27,967
There's a cooking contest.

72
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:29,500
It's sponsored by the LGU.

73
00:03:29,567 --> 00:03:33,167
So technically,
this is your community service.

74
00:03:33,233 --> 00:03:35,900
Wait, is Grandmother Ikay
included the cooking contest?

75
00:03:36,867 --> 00:03:40,367
Yes. It's the best of the best
who cook pinangat.

76
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:44,667
There will be a chef judge
from Manila.

77
00:03:44,733 --> 00:03:45,967
But she's a local from Sorsogon.

78
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:49,700
Wow, for sure Grandmother Ikay
will win.

79
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:51,067
Her pinangat is delicious.

80
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:54,267
You can't really say.
Yes, her pinangat is delicious

81
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:57,267
but sometimes, people's taste
also evolves, right?

82
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,667
Just like you,
you have a lot of attitude

83
00:03:58,733 --> 00:04:00,167
that you got from Manila.

84
00:04:00,233 --> 00:04:00,733
Got it?

85
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,033
You're really picking on me.

86
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:06,000
You know you will miss me
when I go back to Manila.

87
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:10,200
For sure, I will miss
you're being a troublemaker.

88
00:04:10,267 --> 00:04:11,800
And what you say
when you're drunk.

89
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:14,867
What did I say when I was drunk?

90
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,500
Nothing, but you're more active.

91
00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:19,933
Animal.

92
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:21,367
Let's go.

93
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:24,967
This is beautiful.

94
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:27,633
Wow!

95
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:32,400
It's beautiful.

96
00:04:32,467 --> 00:04:35,133
Wow, look at the colors.

97
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,967
You know,
sunflowers always face...

98
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:40,900
- the sun.
- The sun,

99
00:04:40,967 --> 00:04:42,767
that's why it's called
sunflowers.

100
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,300
Oh my God.

101
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,700
And at night?

102
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:46,533
They sleep.

103
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:52,667
It's beautiful.

104
00:04:52,733 --> 00:04:53,600
I love it.

105
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:36,467
Grandmother Ikay.

106
00:05:36,533 --> 00:05:38,033
Hey...

107
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:41,700
good thing you arrived.

108
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:45,067
I have supporters now.

109
00:05:45,133 --> 00:05:47,233
I'm so nervous.

110
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:49,000
Grandmother Ikay, you can do it.

111
00:05:49,067 --> 00:05:51,467
Your pinangat
is already a winner.

112
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:54,467
Thank you and you still believe
in me.

113
00:05:54,533 --> 00:06:00,233
But I heard they will make
a secret recipe.

114
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:04,700
My only secret in cooking
is being happy.

115
00:06:04,767 --> 00:06:06,967
Because if you're happy
with what you do,

116
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:08,367
your food will be delicious.

117
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,633
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

118
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:12,900
Thank you, thank you.

119
00:06:14,067 --> 00:06:15,333
Let's fix this.

120
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:20,633
That's beautiful.

121
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:21,933
- Wait, I'll fix this first.
 - Are you okay, Grandmother?

122
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:22,533
Yes.

123
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,867
What else do you need?

124
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:25,467
Can you still manage?

125
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:28,733
You might pass out
before you cook.

126
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,333
Yes.

127
00:06:35,133 --> 00:06:36,333
Mr. Nanding, thank you

128
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,900
for letting us stay here
in your house.

129
00:06:38,967 --> 00:06:40,100
I'm also sorry last night

130
00:06:40,167 --> 00:06:42,000
if you didn't fall asleep
right away.

131
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:44,033
No, that's okay.

132
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:48,233
It's us who should apologize
to you because we disturbed you.

133
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,333
That's nothing.

134
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,700
Besides, you're no longer
a stranger to us.

135
00:06:52,767 --> 00:06:57,233
When the time comes that you
and Sebastian will get married,

136
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,567
you should get me
as your Principal Sponsor.

137
00:06:58,633 --> 00:07:00,300
Yes, of course, Mr. Nanding.

138
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:04,600
You have to be our godfather
so when Tiffany becomes my wife,

139
00:07:04,667 --> 00:07:07,467
there's someone
who will give us advice

140
00:07:07,533 --> 00:07:09,967
if we have a misunderstanding.

141
00:07:10,933 --> 00:07:12,800
She is the jealous type.

142
00:07:12,867 --> 00:07:16,467
Basti, who would not be jealous?

143
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:19,500
Your dimples attract women.

144
00:07:19,567 --> 00:07:21,767
You, too. You know Tiffany,

145
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,500
I fell in love
with that dimples of yours.

146
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:27,633
Why?

147
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:30,500
- There's a mosquito.
- Yes, there's a mosquito.

148
00:07:30,567 --> 00:07:31,933
- Thank you, James.
- Mr. Ben!

149
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,233
Good morning.

150
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,767
Sir, is your jeep okay now?

151
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:38,300
- It's okay now.
- Good.

152
00:07:38,367 --> 00:07:39,533
You three can go home.

153
00:07:41,133 --> 00:07:42,200
Yes!

154
00:07:42,267 --> 00:07:44,200
You should eat first.
Have a seat.

155
00:07:44,267 --> 00:07:45,933
- Your breakfast is delicious.
- Let's eat, Sir.

156
00:08:27,933 --> 00:08:31,233
Hey, Celeste
is really very beautiful.

157
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:34,267
Grandmother, you startled me.

158
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:37,300
You're caught already.

159
00:08:37,367 --> 00:08:41,300
Now, tell me you're not in love
with her.

160
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,033
You talk too much, Grandmother.

161
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,200
It just so happened
when you saw me

162
00:08:45,267 --> 00:08:46,300
the camera was focused on her.

163
00:08:46,367 --> 00:08:47,300
I'll be taking a video
of everything.

164
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:49,567
You're denying it.

165
00:08:49,633 --> 00:08:50,333
You're caught already.

166
00:08:51,467 --> 00:08:52,467
You talk a lot.

167
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:53,933
Celeste might hear
what you're saying.

168
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:54,533
Hey...

169
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:57,433
- There's nothing.
- What are you arguing about?

170
00:09:00,567 --> 00:09:03,100
Nothing.
Grandmother is getting ready.

171
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,567
- Yes.
- Go ahead, Grandmother.

172
00:09:04,633 --> 00:09:05,833
Good luck, Grandmother.

173
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:09,633
Thank you.

174
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:15,567
Good luck.

175
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:50,167
We will time this contest.

176
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:54,967
The contestants
will begin simultaneously.

177
00:09:55,033 --> 00:09:59,267
We will give 30 minutes

178
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:03,800
to cook the famous dish
here in Sorsogon.

179
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,433
That is the pinangat or tilmok.

180
00:10:08,767 --> 00:10:11,933
Whoever the judge will choose
is the winner.

181
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:15,600
The judge's decision is final.

182
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:19,833
And the time begins now!

183
00:12:25,067 --> 00:12:25,933
Your saliva is dripping.

184
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:36,933
Hello, Basti?

185
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,000
Yes, we're okay.

186
00:12:40,933 --> 00:12:41,133
Bye.

187
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:45,000
You were just together earlier.

188
00:12:45,067 --> 00:12:46,233
What is this?

189
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:49,000
Don't tell me you've decided
to be his real girlfriend?

190
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:50,200
Is this a part of your scheme?

191
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:54,433
James, he was just asking
how we are.

192
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,833
Why didn't he call me?

193
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:58,200
Because you are always fighting.

194
00:12:58,267 --> 00:12:59,600
You're always jealous.

195
00:13:00,533 --> 00:13:02,800
It's because I see something
to be jealous of.

196
00:13:04,733 --> 00:13:05,500
You know you are sweet.

197
00:13:06,733 --> 00:13:08,233
You hold hands. He hugs you.

198
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,300
You have a lot of pictures
together than the two of us.

199
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,167
You sleep next to each other.

200
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:15,367
It looks like
you're enjoying it.

201
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:20,400
And you're doing this
in front of my face.

202
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:21,967
What? We will fight about this
again?

203
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,533
James, don't you get it?

204
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:27,100
It's just a freaking show,
James.

205
00:13:27,167 --> 00:13:28,767
For me, it's not.

206
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:30,400
This is not a show.

207
00:13:30,467 --> 00:13:30,967
You like him.

208
00:13:32,433 --> 00:13:33,567
You can't deny that to me.

209
00:13:33,633 --> 00:13:34,433
How dare you!

210
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:37,200
Take back what you said.

211
00:13:37,267 --> 00:13:37,467
No.

212
00:13:38,867 --> 00:13:39,500
That's what I see.

213
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:42,567
- And that's how I feel.
- So that's it.

214
00:13:42,633 --> 00:13:43,933
Do you see your girlfriend
as a flirt?

215
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,933
If that's the case,
we should break up

216
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:49,600
because it's embarrassing
for you.

217
00:13:49,667 --> 00:13:52,200
You are a very good person
and your girlfriend is a flirt.

218
00:15:43,267 --> 00:15:44,667
The presentation is beautiful.

219
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:05,067
Your presentation
is also beautiful.

220
00:16:05,133 --> 00:16:06,533
Did you put this?

221
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:06,933
Did you put a lot?

222
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:08,533
Let's taste it.

223
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:30,033
You put this and you have that.

224
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:30,933
Did you put a lot of chilies?

225
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:48,700
It's delicious.

226
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:50,267
It's delicious.

227
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:32,633
Grandmother Ikay?

228
00:18:35,133 --> 00:18:35,767
Mikoy!

229
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:39,567
Grandmother Ikay, this is Hazel!

230
00:18:42,067 --> 00:18:42,567
Mikoy!

231
00:18:45,233 --> 00:18:46,333
Grandmother Ikay!

232
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:50,133
There's nobody there.

233
00:18:51,467 --> 00:18:55,100
Do you know where Mikoy
and Grandmother Ikay are?

234
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:57,300
Grandmother Ikay
is in the capitol.

235
00:18:57,367 --> 00:19:00,200
But I don't know where Mikoy is.

236
00:19:01,833 --> 00:19:02,733
Okay, thank you.

237
00:19:31,967 --> 00:19:33,733
Hazel, is that you?

238
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:35,533
May-May.

239
00:19:37,767 --> 00:19:38,200
Hey.

240
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:40,667
I just arrived.

241
00:19:42,067 --> 00:19:44,100
Have you seen Grandmother Ikay
and Mikoy?

242
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:46,333
They're inside.

243
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:48,667
I dropped by to see them.

244
00:19:48,733 --> 00:19:49,833
Let's go. Come with me.

245
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:51,567
I want to see Mikoy.

246
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:53,933
You go ahead.
I'll just park this.

247
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,533
Okay, take care.

248
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:55,967
Okay.

249
00:20:05,233 --> 00:20:08,333
Of course,
the first prize winner

250
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:13,100
is no other than
the Eatery Queen,

251
00:20:13,167 --> 00:20:16,400
it's Grandmother Ikay!

252
00:20:20,633 --> 00:20:21,867
Congratulations!

253
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:22,967
That was very delicious.

254
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:25,233
- Thank you so much.
- Nothing is as delicious.

255
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:26,033
Thank you.

256
00:20:42,667 --> 00:20:46,133
Congratulations,
Grandmother Ikay.

257
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,867
- I told you.
- Grandmother.

258
00:20:47,933 --> 00:20:50,733
- Oh my...
- I told you, you would win.

259
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:52,867
How is your wound?

260
00:20:52,933 --> 00:20:54,067
This is nothing.

261
00:20:54,133 --> 00:20:54,900
It's nothing serious.

262
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:58,700
You are the Queen of Pinangat.

263
00:20:58,767 --> 00:21:00,967
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

264
00:21:01,033 --> 00:21:03,433
I'm also happy for you.

265
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:06,400
Even if you and Mikoy
didn't end up together,

266
00:21:06,467 --> 00:21:07,833
I'm still happy

267
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:11,300
because you fulfilled
your dreams in life.

268
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:14,300
Despite you being glamorous,

269
00:21:14,367 --> 00:21:15,600
being modern,

270
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:20,400
being a good person
is still in your heart.

271
00:21:21,567 --> 00:21:23,867
I love you, Grandmother Ikay.

272
00:21:23,933 --> 00:21:25,300
Thank you, thank you.

273
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:26,233
You talk too much.

274
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:28,633
You're really something else.

275
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:29,933
- It's beautiful.
- Yes.

276
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,200
- Another trophy for you.

277
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:33,133
Mikoy?

278
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:37,333
Hazel.

279
00:21:50,033 --> 00:21:51,067
Grandmother Ikay!

280
00:21:52,067 --> 00:21:52,833
Hello...

281
00:21:54,267 --> 00:21:55,367
congratulations.

282
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:56,967
Thank you.

283
00:21:59,733 --> 00:22:00,167
Hi...

284
00:22:02,067 --> 00:22:02,967
I'm Hazel.

285
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:24,633
I'm Mikoy's girlfriend.

286
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:50,600
Come on, let's talk.

287
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:53,200
Excuse me.

288
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:20,133
Grandmother.

289
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:25,833
What are you doing here?

290
00:23:26,833 --> 00:23:28,433
Is that how you will welcome me?

291
00:23:29,667 --> 00:23:31,900
What I mean is
what are you doing here?

292
00:23:32,767 --> 00:23:33,267
I missed you.

293
00:23:34,833 --> 00:23:35,700
You know what I mean.

294
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,367
Well, I just wanted
to surprise you.

295
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,100
You know me.

296
00:23:42,167 --> 00:23:45,000
But the truth is I missed you.

297
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:50,733
I know it was my idea
to study abroad.

298
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:53,333
And I'm always going
to be forever grateful

299
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,233
that you allowed me.

300
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:56,967
You supported me
and you understood

301
00:23:57,067 --> 00:23:58,600
all my decisions in life.

302
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:01,767
Actually, it went really well.

303
00:24:01,833 --> 00:24:05,067
I got a good offer
from a big company abroad

304
00:24:05,133 --> 00:24:06,633
after I finished my MBA,

305
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:10,133
but even if everything
is going so well,

306
00:24:11,167 --> 00:24:12,267
it's like I'm not happy.

307
00:24:13,667 --> 00:24:15,200
Then it hit me.

308
00:24:15,267 --> 00:24:18,333
Do I want to establish myself
away from my family,

309
00:24:19,533 --> 00:24:20,500
away from roots?

310
00:24:22,533 --> 00:24:23,933
Away from the person I love,

311
00:24:25,633 --> 00:24:26,400
away from you.

312
00:24:29,233 --> 00:24:33,100
It was so foolish of me to think
that there's a better life

313
00:24:33,167 --> 00:24:35,167
waiting for me in America.

314
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:37,833
When all I ever need
is right here,

315
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:39,100
with you.

316
00:24:39,167 --> 00:24:39,867
So here I am,

317
00:24:42,267 --> 00:24:44,567
asking you
if we can start again.

318
00:24:47,367 --> 00:24:48,767
Can you give us another chance?

319
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:18,367
Hazel is the name of the one
who hugged Mikoy.

320
00:25:18,433 --> 00:25:19,800
You know, it's really none
of my business.

321
00:25:19,867 --> 00:25:22,533
Even if they kiss, I don't care.

322
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:23,833
Basti, what do you want?

323
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:26,067
I just want you to taste
my mother's cooking.

324
00:25:26,133 --> 00:25:27,933
But if you're not in the mood,

325
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,100
that's okay.

326
00:25:29,167 --> 00:25:30,133
I will leave.

327
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,533
- Wait.
- You know Grandmother,

328
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:34,767
I think there's nothing wrong
if we try to start again.

329
00:25:34,833 --> 00:25:36,233
We had a good relationship.

330
00:25:36,333 --> 00:25:37,900
Not once did she give up on me.

331
00:25:37,967 --> 00:25:39,500
Are you sure about that?

332
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:40,967
I was really surprised

333
00:25:41,033 --> 00:25:42,867
that Mikoy had a history
with that woman.

334
00:25:42,933 --> 00:25:45,733
His taste for women
is already a bit doubtful.

335
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:49,333
Wait, aren't we talking
about your former boyfriend?

336
00:25:49,400 --> 00:25:52,433
I'm also surprised myself
why I fell for him back then.

337
00:25:52,500 --> 00:25:55,567
So, you think Aurelia
is being desperate?

338
00:25:55,633 --> 00:25:57,167
- I don't know.
- You don't know

339
00:25:58,333 --> 00:26:00,333
or you just don't want
to say it?

340
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:01,833
Good morning.

341
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:03,200
We have a visitor.

342
00:26:03,267 --> 00:26:05,200
It's Hazel? What is she doing
there?

343
00:26:05,267 --> 00:26:06,267
I have no idea.

344
00:26:06,333 --> 00:26:09,267
But I feel
there will be a cock fight.
